    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-08T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-08T06:00:00-05:00" n="487"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d487">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-08T18:00:00+07:00"
                            >November 8, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 8—1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1800. 1. We are now informed by a member that PPC investigation party expects to
                    leave next week for Yenan. (Retel 1781, November 4, 5 p.m.) Members of party are
                    said to feel that hopes of Kmt–CCP<note n="55a" xml:id="d487fn55a">Chinese
                        Communist Party.</note>
                    <pb facs="0686" n="672" xml:id="pg_672"/> settlement are small but are
                    nevertheless worth exploring. We are of opinion that mission is unlikely to
                    result in any concrete accomplishment.</p>
                <p>2. Local office of CCP newspaper was reportedly raided by local authorities [on]
                    4th and quantity of Communist literature seized.</p>
                <p>3. According to local representative of independent guerilla group operating in
                    Shantung (Redes 072 [<hi rend="italic">3072</hi>], October 18<note n="56"
                        xml:id="d487fn56">Not printed.</note>), Communist Eighth Route and New
                    Fourth Armies have recently launched military attacks on independent guerilla
                    areas in Shantung and North Kiangsu in endeavor to liquidate latter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
